Section Summary: The introduction to Will Bradley's chap book highlights his significant impact on American graphic arts, bringing a fresh and modern style to a field that was previously stagnant. Bradley's work was influenced by European artists, but he developed a unique American style that was bold, free, and exuberant. The chapter "The Boy Printer of Ishpeming" tells the story of Bradley's childhood, growing up in Massachusetts and later moving to Northern Michigan with his mother. Bradley's early interest in art and printing is evident, and he spends much of his childhood dreaming of becoming an artist and finding ways to pursue his passion despite financial constraints. Through his determination and talent, Bradley would go on to become a pioneering figure in American graphic design.
